## ranges

Defines the mapping between child bus addresses and parent bus addresses. An empty `ranges` means a 1:1 mapping. Each entry is `<child-addr parent-addr length>`.

```dts
/* arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/sm8550.dtsi */
pcie0: pci@1c00000 {
    #address-cells = <3>;
    #size-cells = <2>;
    ranges = <0x01000000 0x0 0x00000000 0x0 0x01c10000 0x0 0x00010000>;
};
```
